{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3526506,"name":"AmoryG","username":"AmoryG","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/amoryg/{size}/176897_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-13T22:10:57.523Z","cooked":"<p>I’m happy to (finally) announce the 2025 release of the <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span> Web Components dashboard! <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/tada.png?v=12" title=":tada:" class="emoji" alt=":tada:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/5/a/5ac3556f0d9fc1649abb57ffbeb732be6fcc01fe.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/5ac3556f0d9fc1649abb57ffbeb732be6fcc01fe" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/5/a/5ac3556f0d9fc1649abb57ffbeb732be6fcc01fe_2_690x322.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="cWVtjTytl64oOHW1j4ir8HVnxDg" width="690" height="322" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/5/a/5ac3556f0d9fc1649abb57ffbeb732be6fcc01fe_2_690x322.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/5/a/5ac3556f0d9fc1649abb57ffbeb732be6fcc01fe_2_1035x483.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/5/a/5ac3556f0d9fc1649abb57ffbeb732be6fcc01fe_2_1380x644.png 2x" data-dominant-color="2A2B2B"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">1530×715 117 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p><span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span> Web Components (FWC) is a project started in 2020 that provides tools to help teams create custom web based dashboards. A couple years ago I created a Shuffleboard like application built using the FWC <a href="https://frc-web-components.github.io/storybook/?path=/docs/frc-introduction--docs" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">component library</a>. Since then some great new dashboard alternatives such as <a href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/elastic-2025-a-lot-of-little-things/472475">Elastic</a> have been released which fill the needs of most teams. However, if you’re interested in creating custom dashboards and enjoy using web technologies I encourage you to try this project out!</p>
<h2><a name="p-3526506-links-1" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-links-1"></a>Links</h2>
<p>The app can be installed from here: <a href="https://github.com/frc-web-components/app/releases/latest" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Release FWC Dashboard 2025.1.3 · frc-web-components/app · GitHub</a></p>
<p>A web hosted version of the dashboard is also available if you’d like to try it.  You can even connect to your simulated robot right from your browser: <a href="https://frc-web-components.github.io/dashboard/" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">FWC Dashboard</a></p>
<p>Dashboard documentation can be found here: <a href="https://github.com/frc-web-components/frc-web-components/blob/master/docs/dashboard.md" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">frc-web-components/docs/dashboard.md at master · frc-web-components/frc-web-components</a></p>
<p>Plugin documentation can be found here: <a href="https://github.com/frc-web-components/frc-web-components/blob/master/docs/plugins.md" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">frc-web-components/docs/plugins.md at master · frc-web-components/frc-web-components</a></p>
<h1><a name="p-3526506-h-2025-updates-2" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-h-2025-updates-2"></a>2025 Updates</h1>
<p>This year the dashboard app has been completely refactored and now uses <a href="https://react.dev/" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">React</a> for rendering and <a href="https://redux.js.org/" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Redux</a> for state management. The project previously relied on a lot of custom stuff as well as some lesser known libraries such as <a href="https://lit.dev/" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Lit</a>. I found this to be a turn off for would-be developers looking to contribute. I decided to switch to a software stack that was more familiar and approachable. This was a lot of work and contributed to the late release, but I’m hoping long term the switch will make it easier for myself and others to continue supporting the project. There’s still work left to be done on documentation and probably a few bugs that will need to fixed, but I wanted to make a post about this before it becomes too late in the season.</p>
<p>Aside from refactors, other significant updates have been made this year, particularly to the user interface:</p>
<h2><a name="p-3526506-more-flexible-layouts-3" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-more-flexible-layouts-3"></a>More flexible layouts</h2>
<p>A new layout manager was added powered by <a href="https://github.com/caplin/FlexLayout" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">React FlexLayout</a>. Tabs can now be rearranged into rows, columns, and tab groups:</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/b/a/ba0189075c2173e7adc63e5708160de60d9858ed.gif" alt="Layout Manager" data-base62-sha1="qxu67N69cDaUCTKTdYAHsqEA8ln" width="630" height="500" class="animated"></p>
<h2><a name="p-3526506-add-components-directly-from-sources-4" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-add-components-directly-from-sources-4"></a>Add components directly from sources</h2>
<p>This is a frequently requested feature from other dashboards such as Elastic and Shuffleboard:</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/f/3/f375ff933ee9c02b23aa98b5586434cb4a174b5f.gif" alt="dragging-sources" data-base62-sha1="yJKPO2lAMOsttB5gSLWswlaaOZx" width="690" height="355" class="animated"></p>
<h2><a name="p-3526506-grid-layouts-5" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-grid-layouts-5"></a>Grid Layouts</h2>
<p>Components can now be arranged in a grid:</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/a/6/a676467ca7a8932c52d3ef306b953a877a26a342.gif" alt="grid-layout" data-base62-sha1="nKAF9NSovqtYdLrClmkCIE3aLQe" width="690" height="355" class="animated"></p>
<h2><a name="p-3526506-converting-components-6" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-converting-components-6"></a>Converting components</h2>
<p>Components can be changed to other components that accept the same type of source that it’s current assigned. This can be done by right clicking a selected component and selecting from the <strong>Show As…</strong> menu:</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/2/7/27272fde8d8544a8674c14460f37ee8bdd3d643d.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/27272fde8d8544a8674c14460f37ee8bdd3d643d" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/2/7/27272fde8d8544a8674c14460f37ee8bdd3d643d_2_690x288.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="5AmzU0joUFhrYWzrigWV1WsuPSd" width="690" height="288" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/2/7/27272fde8d8544a8674c14460f37ee8bdd3d643d_2_690x288.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/2/7/27272fde8d8544a8674c14460f37ee8bdd3d643d_2_1035x432.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/2/7/27272fde8d8544a8674c14460f37ee8bdd3d643d.png 2x" data-dominant-color="1F2021"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">1197×500 38.8 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/4/b/4b7c1c83e23c1b836bdf4a81b00e2e99544945c1.gif" alt="show as" data-base62-sha1="aLLIuR9isjPr8NO78nAanSGk7Yt" width="611" height="500" class="animated"></p>
<h2><a name="p-3526506-networktables-7" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-networktables-7"></a>NetworkTables</h2>
<p>A lot of the improvements here were pulled from AdvantageScope so a huge thank you to AdvantageScope and its team of developers!</p>
<ul>
<li>NT4 client has been upgraded to 4.1</li>
<li>Added support for structs</li>
<li>The dashboard subscribes to all topics only while editing. While competing only the topics used by your components will be subscribed to.</li>
</ul>
<h2><a name="p-3526506-example-layouts-8" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-example-layouts-8"></a>Example Layouts</h2>
<p>The dashboard now includes built-in layouts which can be opened from the <em>File &gt; Open Example…</em> menu. Currently only a <span class="abbreviation">YAGSL<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Yet Another Generic Swerve Library"></template></span> Swerve layout is available, but more will be added soon:</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/0/b/0b11ca5611c7e9245f36859a86ee232a1de0ab45.gif" alt="examples" data-base62-sha1="1zVmO7WGMLxUhQKZu2mPdmiPGJL" width="690" height="362" class="animated"></p>
<h2><a name="p-3526506-properties-and-sources-9" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-properties-and-sources-9"></a>Properties and sources</h2>
<p>Component behavior can be modified through their properties. Properties can be edited from the “Properties” panel:</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/8/5/85359d5a3a4df2780eeeb729a3ee8d2b9628a95a.gif" alt="update-properties" data-base62-sha1="j0qn5G0Pt6DNttGH7Za91KM4gxY" width="626" height="352" class="animated"></p>
<p>Properties can be externally controlled by binding them to sources. In previous versions you could only bind a source directly to the component. In the 2025 release you can now also bind sources directly to individual properties:</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/b/7/b759cccdfba4f63602d323eb436af7c37efbbf39.gif" alt="prop-sources" data-base62-sha1="q9ZLUqq3Zn5I27cC8Ucct5rHqZj" width="519" height="500" class="animated"></p>
<p>In the image above the NetworkTables “/box” source has 2 children: <em>/box/value</em> and <em>/box/Label</em>. The children are mapped to properties in the component (the keys are converted to camel case, so an exact match is not required). Another source is bound directly to the “trueColor” property.</p>
<h2><a name="p-3526506-plugin-api-10" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-plugin-api-10"></a>Plugin API</h2>
<p>The plugin API is now simpler and more consistent between different front-end frameworks. Plugins can be created using React, Svelte, Lit, and any front-end framework that supports web components.</p>
<p>Here’s an example of a simple component created using the plugin API with React and Svelte:</p>
<h3><a name="p-3526506-react-example-11" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-react-example-11"></a>React example</h3>
<pre data-code-wrap="tsx"><code class="lang-tsx">
import {
  getAssetUrl,
  createComponent,
  numberProp,
} from '@frc-web-components/app';
import './styles.css';

export const myElement = createComponent(
  {
    dashboard: {
      name: 'My React Element',
      description: '',
      defaultSize: { width: 130, height: 50 },
      minSize: { width: 20, height: 20 },
    },
    // primaryProperty is the property a source assigned to the component will bind to
    primaryProperty: 'count',
    // This allows the component to be converted to another component that accepts "Number" as a source type. Used to populate the "Show As..." context submenu
    acceptedSourceTypes: ['Number'],
    // Properties are used to control how the element looks and behaves. They can be bound
    // to external sources such as NetworkTables
    properties: {
      count: numberProp(),
    },
  },
  // The component's properties will be passed as props. The setProperty method can be used for setting a property's value
  ({ count, setProperty }) =&gt; {
    return (
      &lt;button
        className="my-element"
        onClick=
        // This increments the count property value. If a source (such as a NetworkTables topic)
        // is bound to this property it will be updated as well.
        {() =&gt; setProperty('count', count + 1)}
      &gt;
        {/* You can include assets such as images using the getAssetUrl function */}
        &lt;img src={getAssetUrl('party.svg')} alt="party time" /&gt;
        Party Guests: {count}
      &lt;/button&gt;
    );
  },
);

</code></pre>
<p>The component will be typed based on the properties you provide the component:</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/8/c/8c60e08b2fb58f51c3fc036b459ecbb099a15232.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/8c60e08b2fb58f51c3fc036b459ecbb099a15232" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/8/c/8c60e08b2fb58f51c3fc036b459ecbb099a15232.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="k1Qp3wGzs1BUEh1IBVjLrIVpLNg" width="689" height="195" data-dominant-color="232526"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">1207×342 21.7 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>Plugins can be built and imported into your dashboard. Once imported plugin components will be available to add:</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/9/f/9fb62e3800f48a71f8738cea41d24dc9c36d7e38.gif" alt="my-element" data-base62-sha1="mMSeK9oVxNfIcAb1sCCy4jBwlVC" width="626" height="352" class="animated"></p>
<h3><a name="p-3526506-svelte-example-12" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-svelte-example-12"></a>Svelte Example</h3>
<p>(Using an image here because the text is preventing me from creating the topic for some reason)</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/f/d/fdcfb284294aa8a5739c6a6ddbd4e534cb7460ac.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/fdcfb284294aa8a5739c6a6ddbd4e534cb7460ac" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/f/d/fdcfb284294aa8a5739c6a6ddbd4e534cb7460ac.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="AdjMWPIfvFdxE2nCIOG2Q5fmDuI" width="488" height="500" data-dominant-color="252626"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">625×640 25.1 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<pre data-code-wrap="tsx"><code class="lang-tsx">import {
  createWebComponent,
  numberProp,
} from '@frc-web-components/app';
import MyElement from './MyElement.svelte';

export const mySvelteElement = createWebComponent(
  {
    dashboard: {
      name: 'My Svelte Element',
      description: '',
      defaultSize: { width: 130, height: 50 },
      minSize: { width: 20, height: 20 },
    },
    acceptedSourceTypes: ['Number'],
    primaryProperty: 'count',
    properties: {
      count: numberProp(),
    },
  },
  'my-svelte-element',
  MyElement.element!,
);
</code></pre>
<h1><a name="p-3526506-feedback-13" class="anchor" href="#p-3526506-feedback-13"></a>Feedback</h1>
