,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":284,"readers_count":283,"score":56.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":491604,"topic_slug":"frc-web-components-2025-release","display_username":"Eric Ward","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":65,"username":"Joe_Ross","name":"Joe Ross","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/joe_ross/{size}/37_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":35208,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3637 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/frc-web-components-2025-release/491604/7","custom_user_title":"3637 Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3527062,"name":"AmoryG","username":"AmoryG","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/amoryg/{size}/176897_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-14T15:59:58.368Z","cooked":"<p>This is a great idea! It is technically possible to do this by hosting a <a href="https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/net/WebServer.html" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">web server</a> as <a class="mention" href="/u/peter_johnson">@Peter_Johnson</a> mentioned. Here’s an example of this working:</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/4/b/4b02cc19ad372847c1e59e482df62dfb5ec2aa9b.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/4b02cc19ad372847c1e59e482df62dfb5ec2aa9b" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/4/b/4b02cc19ad372847c1e59e482df62dfb5ec2aa9b_2_690x179.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="aHzNOgKuxTn7jIkGzCmpLcUbM83" width="690" height="179" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/4/b/4b02cc19ad372847c1e59e482df62dfb5ec2aa9b_2_690x179.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/4/b/4b02cc19ad372847c1e59e482df62dfb5ec2aa9b_2_1035x268.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/4/b/4b02cc19ad372847c1e59e482df62dfb5ec2aa9b_2_1380x358.png 2x" data-dominant-color="212323"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">1663×432 40.4 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>And here it is running in sim:</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/f/6/f6a3c73e32e42488de7913c16c9bcffb5738f268.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/f6a3c73e32e42488de7913c16c9bcffb5738f268" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/f/6/f6a3c73e32e42488de7913c16c9bcffb5738f268_2_690x291.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="zbSlLE2MwZHQqpDn9K0yoG74jBm" width="690" height="291" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/f/6/f6a3c73e32e42488de7913c16c9bcffb5738f268_2_690x291.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/f/6/f6a3c73e32e42488de7913c16c9bcffb5738f268_2_1035x436.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/f/6/f6a3c73e32e42488de7913c16c9bcffb5738f268.png 2x" data-dominant-color="1F2020"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">1356×572 31.2 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>The biggest issue here is that the dashboard app’s static assets are quite large (9MB total) which could be an issue with the limited network bandwidth you get at competitions. These assets are static so they would only need to be downloaded when the robot first connects, and as long as your browser can cache the files this should only happen once. I think for this to work you’d need a stripped-down version of the dashboard for display purposes only (no editing capabilities) to reduce its size and the ability to export a layout from the app as a file that can be dropped into the deploy folder and served directly from there.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2025-02-14T15:59:58.368Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":287,"readers_count":286,"score":117.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":491604,"topic_slug":"frc-web-components-2025-release","display_username":"AmoryG","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/net/WebServer.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"WebServer (WPILib API 2025.3.1)","clicks":3}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":35208,"username":"bathtubed","name":"Eric Ward","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bathtubed/{size}/220364_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":10380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2423 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/frc-web-components-2025-release/491604/8","custom_user_title":"2423 Mentor","reac