<p>You can save the layout as an html file using the “Export for Web…” feature from the file menu:</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/a/c/ac84a2e0549fbc7111f9c4f7cb2a18b24fed8fcc.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/ac84a2e0549fbc7111f9c4f7cb2a18b24fed8fcc" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/a/c/ac84a2e0549fbc7111f9c4f7cb2a18b24fed8fcc_2_690x468.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="oCaioFKdzRQCvKGXkfb4bwcp1gM" width="690" height="468" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/a/c/ac84a2e0549fbc7111f9c4f7cb2a18b24fed8fcc_2_690x468.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/a/c/ac84a2e0549fbc7111f9c4f7cb2a18b24fed8fcc.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/a/c/ac84a2e0549fbc7111f9c4f7cb2a18b24fed8fcc.png 2x" data-dominant-color="191818"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">872×592 51.2 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>The file should be saved inside the folder containing the fwc build within the deploy directory:</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/c/4/c49e6697ac8f575149649f0929a7631f9491e312.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/c49e6697ac8f575149649f0929a7631f9491e312" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/c/4/c49e6697ac8f575149649f0929a7631f9491e312_2_690x412.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="s3mXhQ29XqZBAJOX3TsTpgc8h2i" width="690" height="412" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/c/4/c49e6697ac8f575149649f0929a7631f9491e312_2_690x412.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/c/4/c49e6697ac8f575149649f0929a7631f9491e312_2_1035x618.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/c/4/c49e6697ac8f575149649f0929a7631f9491e312.png 2x" data-dominant-color="C2C3C3"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">1127×673 31 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>I created an example robot project you can use to experiment with: <a href="https://github.com/frc-web-components/frc-web-components/tree/master/robot-project-examples/WebServer" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">frc-web-components/robot-project-examples/WebServer at master · frc-web-components/frc-web-components</a></p>
<p>Save the html file to the <code>src/main/deploy/dashboard</code> folder:</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/d/4/d48150ef190ee828851686b5069bff872071c0bd.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="ujUhvbfaFSdbaeCHKxmcmyNylWt" width="526" height="452"></p>
<p>Run in sim and you should be good to go:</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/d/5/d589fa8d3ac47b0ea10a4c5ae9886ef6a2be7d49.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/d589fa8d3ac47b0ea10a4c5ae9886ef6a2be7d49" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/d/5/d589fa8d3ac47b0ea10a4c5ae9886ef6a2be7d49_2_690x344.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="ut3jNaTZd5b1T54d5e47Of1wuQ9" width="690" height="344" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/d/5/d589fa8d3ac47b0ea10a4c5ae9886ef6a2be7d49_2_690x344.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/d/5/d589fa8d3ac47b0ea10a4c5ae9886ef6a2be7d49_2_1035x516.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/d/5/d589fa8d3ac47b0ea10a4c5ae9886ef6a2be7d49_2_1380x688.png 2x" data-dominant-color="5D5F62"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">1756×876 113 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>Note: This is still experimental and the build hasn’t been optimized for hosting from the roborio. It’s still a 9MB monster and has most of the editing capabilities of the dashboard app. Also this feature doesn’t currently support plugins. Still working on that but I thought this at least will help you get started.</p>","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2025-02-16T17:18:43.799Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":231,"readers_count":230,"score":106.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":491604,"topic_slug":"frc-web-components-2025-release","display_username":"AmoryG","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/frc-web-components/frc-web-components/tree/master/robot-project-examples/WebServer","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"frc-web-components/robot-project-examples/WebServer at master · frc-web-components/frc-web-components · GitHub","clicks":3},{"url":"https://github.com/frc-web-components/app/releases/tag/app-v1.2.0","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Release FWC Dashboard 2025.2.0 · frc-web-components/app · GitHub","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":35208,"username":"bathtubed","name":"Eric Ward","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bathtubed/{size}/220364_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":10380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2423 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/frc-web-components-2025-release/491604/11","custom_user_title":"2423 Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1},{"id":"hugs","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3528803,"name":"AmoryG","username":"AmoryG","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/amoryg/{size}/176897_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-16T17:24:43.549Z","cooked":"<p>I was definitely conflicted about moving away from lit. I’m a big fan of web components and relying on web standards vs. libraries like react. I was hoping Lit would catch on more since I first started the project back in 2020, but adoption has been pretty slow. That said, even though the dashboard app is now built with react you can still build components and plugins using lit, svelte and any other framework that supports web components (at least theoretically since there’s many I haven’t tried).</p>","post_number":12,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2025-02-16T17:24:43.549Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":10,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":183,"readers_count":182,"score":51.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":491604,"topic_slug":"frc-web-components-2025-release","display_username":"AmoryG","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":4297,"username":"Andrew_Schreiber","name":"Andrew Schreiber","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/andrew_schreiber/{size}/209563_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":10380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2423 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/frc-web-components-2025-release/491604/12","custom_user_title":"2423 Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3529019,"name":"Gavin Kistner","username":"Phrogz","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/phrogz/{size}/217285_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-16T20:52:42.306Z","cooked":"<p>Thank you for this. My team (and I) would very much like to use this. I’m sad to <a href="https://github.com/frc-web-components/app/issues/20" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">report that the .dmg does not work</a> for macOS, and I’m embarrassed to <a href="https://github.com/frc-web-components/frc-web-components/issues/192" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">admit that I can’t figure out</a> the first step for how to see/use anything from the repo.</p>
<p>For the app, anything I can do to help debug the issue?</p>
<p>For the repo, is there a step I’m missing? Is <code>pnpm dev</code> supposed to launch a GUI?</p>","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2025-02-16T20:58:35.333Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":11,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":183,"readers_count":182,"score":61.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":491604,"topic_slug":"frc-web-components-2025-release","display_username":"Gavin Kistner","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/frc-web-components/frc-web-components/issues/192","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Cannot figure out how to launch the dashboard · Issue #192 · frc-web-components/frc-web-components · GitHub","clicks":1},{"url":"https://github.com/frc-web-components/app/issues/20","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"v1.2 .dmg does not work on macOS · Issue #20 · frc-web-components/app · GitHub","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":10380,"username":"AmoryG","name":"AmoryG","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/amoryg/{size}/176897_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":61711,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/frc-web-components-2025-release/491604/13","custom_user_title":"Programming Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3529097,"name":"AmoryG","username":"AmoryG","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/amoryg/{size}/176897_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-16T22:39:18.282Z","cooked":"<p>Hi <a class="mention" href="/u/phrogz">@Phrogz</a>, I’m sorry for the trouble, I admit I have not done a lot of testing on macOS and I appreciate your efforts to debug the issue. Are you by chance seeing an error that looks like this?</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/d/9/d9d12fa005b3fcb4283fec3f5c182d183ca07d41.jpeg" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="v4TMZ9jt3EkoFM8TqfksN9vCMHT" width="437" height="380"></p>
<p>There’s a process for <a href="https://v1.tauri.app/v1/guides/distribution/sign-macos/" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">signing and notarizing</a> a macOS app that I haven’t gone through, so if you’re seeing this issue then it’s likely its being blocked. I had to get around this issue with the following command:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="bash"><code class="lang-bash">xattr -d com.apple.quarantine /path/to/app/FRC\ Web\ Components.app
</code></pre>
<p>Are you running a mac with one of the newer apple silicon chips, or one of the older intel ones? I’ve only tested with my M2 macbook pro so there might be issues I’m not aware of on different models.</p>
<p>As far as developing in that repo you were on the right track, but unfortunately the documentation is very confusing and out of date. I’ll spend some time updating the docs and address the concerns you posted in the issue and this thread here.</p>
<p>To run the app you’ll have to first run <code>pnpm dev</code> as you’ve already done. This builds the other packages the dashboard relies on and watches for changes. Once that is done in a separate terminal you’ll have to run <code>pnpm dashboard:dev</code> which launches the dashboard in the browser using vite.</p>
<p>However, what you probably want is run in the tauri app: <a href="https://github.com/frc-web-components/app" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">frc-web-components/app: Tauri app for <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span> Web Components dashboard</a></p>
<p>This requires rust as well as npm. Once cloned you’ll have to run <code>npm install</code> and then <code>npm run tauri:dev</code> to launch the app. I’ll also add developer documentation to this repo as well.</p>","post_number":14,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2025-02-16T22:39:18.282Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":13,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":196,"readers_count":195,"score":89.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":491604,"topic_slug":"frc-web-components-2025-release","display_username":"AmoryG","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://v1.tauri.app/v1/guides/distribution/sign-macos/","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Code Signing macOS Applications | Tauri Apps","clicks":2},{"url":"https://github.com/frc-web-components/app","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - frc-web-components/app: Tauri app for FRC Web Components dashboard","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":61711,"username":"Phrogz","name":"Gavin Kistner","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/phrogz/{size}/217285_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":10380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2423 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/frc-web-components-2025-release/491604/14","custom_user_title":"2423 Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3566787,"name":"Antônio Miranda De Assis ","username":"toninhowow","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/8c91f0/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-24T13:23:25.036Z","cooked":"<p>Hello, how are you, Amory? I was looking through all your documentation about <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span> WEB Components, because I’m working on a robot project that needs a front-end with a dynamic and complete interface. I’m using Studica Robotics Hardware, which in general all the programming is the same as <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span>, but it only supports VScode and WPILIB version 2020. My current problem is that I can’t pull the encoder values ​​to run on my front-end. Do you have an example just to pull the value?</p>","post_number":15,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2025-03-24T13:23:25.036Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":155,"readers_count":154,"score":56.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":491604,"topic_slug":"frc-web-components-2025-release","display_username":"Antônio Miranda De Assis ","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":74540,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/frc-web-components-2025-release/491604/15","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3567832,"name":"AmoryG","username":"AmoryG","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/amoryg/{size}/176897_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-25T05:42:08.691Z","cooked":"<p>Hello <a class="mention" href="/u/toninhowow">@toninhowow</a>, are you interested in using the app, or building a custom dashboard using the component library? The dashboard app uses a newer version of NetworkTables (4.1) and is incompatible with older versions of WPILib which uses NetworkTables version 3. The dashboard can communicate directly with an NT4 server since it uses websockets, while back in the NT3 days additional tools like <a href="https://github.com/robotpy/pynetworktables2js" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">pynetworktables2js</a> needed to be used as well. If you’d like I can assist with creating a plugin that allows the dashboard to communicate with an NT3 server using pynetworktables2js. Alternatively, I can help get you started with a React, Svelte or some other web based template that uses the component library and pynetworktables2js?</p>","post_number":16,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2025-03-25T05:42:08.691Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":15,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":155,"readers_count":154,"score":46.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":491604,"topic_slug":"frc-web-components-2025-release","display_username":"AmoryG","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/robotpy/pynetworktables2js","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - robotpy/pynetworktables2js: Forwards NetworkTables traffic to a web page, allowing you to write custom dashboards for your robot using HTML/Javascript","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":74540,"username":"toninhowow","name":"Antônio Miranda De Assis ","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/8c91f0/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":10380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2423 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/frc-web-components-2025-release/491604/16","custom_user_title":"2423 Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3567994,"name":"Antônio Miranda De Assis ","username":"toninhowow","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/8c91f0/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-25T14:24:31.508Z","cooked":"<p>I am interested in creating a custom dashboard! So far, I have completed the full programming of the Robot using the 2020 version of WPILib. In my WEB interface, I set up the Operator’s camera by creating a simple action stream using USB port 1181 along with the robot’s IP address. I also added a JS function to capture the image and achieve my goal of displaying the date and the encoder value—which, in the robot’s programming, is already calculated in millimeters. However, I am really lost on how to retrieve the encoder value. I looked into pynetworktables2js, ran it in my WEB project, and also implemented the <a href="https://github.com/frc-web-components/frc-web-components/releases" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">FRCWebComponents</a> script that you shared!  Can you tell me what the next step is?</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/4X/8/5/8/8583475919fd7e8fcfe6e94a5a06aed852f14d23.jpeg" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/8583475919fd7e8fcfe6e94a5a06aed852f14d23" title="imagem_2025-03-20T18-47-57-686Z"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/4X/8/5/8/8583475919fd7e8fcfe6e94a5a06aed852f14d23_2_517x291.jpeg" alt="imagem_2025-03-20T18-47-57-686Z" data-base62-sha1="j36LxWpUc8rOPtnfLIy2D0qsQjV" width="517" height="291" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/4X/8/5/8/8583475919fd7e8fcfe6e94a5a06aed852f14d23_2_517x291.jpeg, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/4X/8/5/8/8583475919fd7e8fcfe6e94a5a06aed852f14d23_2_775x436.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/4X/8/5/8/8583475919fd7e8fcfe6e94a5a06aed852f14d23_2_1034x582.jpeg 2x" data-dominant-color="606363"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">imagem_2025-03-20T18-47-57-686Z</span><span class="informations">1920×1080 226 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>","post_number":17,"post_type":1,"posts_count":29,"updated_at":"2025-03-25T16:14:35.653Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":16,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":8,"reads":160,"readers_count":159,"score":77.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":491604,"topic_slug":"frc-web-components-2025-release","display_username":"Antônio Miranda De Assis ","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/frc-web-components/frc-web-com